e^{-x}\text{sin}(2xy)
(\ast)
\dfrac{\sin^2 x}{x}
\int_u^v \sin (2xy)\,dy.
1
\frac{d}{dy} \frac{\sin^2 (xy)}{x} = \frac{2\sin(xy)\cos (xy)\cdot x}{x} = 2\sin(xy)\cos(xy) = \sin(2xy).
\frac{\sin^2 x}{x} = \int_0^1 \sin(2xy)\,dy
x > 0
\int_0^\infty e^{-x}\int_0^1 \sin (2xy)\,dy \,dx = \int_0^1 \int_0^\infty e^{-x}\sin (2xy)\,dx\,dy.
